40: DRAW or NOT the MESH QUALITY
Demand or suppress the drawing of FE qualities between 0 and 1

For a TRIANGLE the QUALITY = c * r /R where
r is the inscribed     radius circle of the triangle
R is the circumscribed radius circle of the triangle
c is a coefficient to have 1 for the regular triangle

For a QUADRANGLE, the QUALITY is the MINIMUM of the 4 angles
    1 - abs ( PI/2 - angle ) / PI/2

For a TETRAHEDRON the QUALITY = c * r /R where
r is the inscribed     radius circle of the tetrahedron
R is the circumscribed radius circle of the tetrahedron
c is a coefficient to have 1 for the regular tetrahedron

For a PENTAHEDRON or HEXAHEDRON, its QUALITY is the
MINIMUM of their FACE QUALITIES

41: QUALITY of LAST DRAWN SURFACE or VOLUME
